You're right, I got carried away with the locking system and broke the core pipeline. Let me trace the full flow and fix it properly.

The complete pipeline should be:

```
ARCore camera preview (GLSurfaceView)
    ↓
Tap scan → PixelCopy grabs frame
    ↓
ML Kit Text Recognition → text blocks + bounding boxes
    ↓
TypographyAnalyzer → font size, colour, bg colour per block
    ↓
InpaintingEraser → removes original text from bitmap
    ↓
TranslationProcessor (ML Kit Translate) → translated strings
    ↓
FlagshipBillboard → bitmap with inpainted bg + translated text
    ↓
ARCore hit-test → 3 anchors per block on real surface
    ↓
AnchorLock → builds confidence → freezes pose
    ↓
GL renders billboard texture locked to surface
```

